The National Union of Mineworkers National Health and Safety Committee (NAHSCO) is deeply concerned with the loss of life that continues to occur at workplaces. NUM statement: NAHSCO demand that the Department of Labour (DOL) and the Department of Mineral Resources (DMR) Inspectorate work with the National Union of Mineworkers shop stewards to improve the state of health and safety in the Mining; Construction and Energy. This is after NAHSCO recently held a two days meeting to deal with health and safety issues that affect workers in sectors where the National Union of Mineworkers organises. NAHSCO pronounced on the following critical health and safety issues: